properties.areaDesc: Coastal Waters from Stonington, ME to Port Clyde, ME out 25 NM; Coastal Waters from Port Clyde, ME to Cape Elizabeth, ME out 25 NM
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 7 at 2:36AM EST until February 8 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Gray ME
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 30 to 40 kt with gusts up to 45 kt and seas
11 to 16 feet expected.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Port Clyde, ME to Stonington, ME
out to 25 NM.

* WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 1 AM EST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A few gusts to 50kts are possible in the
southernmost areas as the low passes by this evening.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 1 AM EST SATURDAY
